storyInfo:
Tomimi plays her hand, but without knowing the Doctor had it all figured out long before. It's over.
In the end, Tomimi, Zumama, and Kemar all decide to go to Rhodes Island.

attributes.content: It's over, Tomimi.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: ...N-No it's not!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Nurul, Peta!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Doctor!
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: Doctor!
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: If you don't want your friends getting hurt...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Don't make me angry, Tomimi!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: ...I won't stop until you promise you'll stay, Gavial!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Help me, Doctor!
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: Doctor, I'm scared... Waaahhh...
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.options: Did you finish your task?;......;Don't be scared! I'm going to save you!

attributes.content: Doctor, please. The girl's pouring her heart out here, it wouldn't kill you to work with her.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: The people here are simple. Honestly, it hurts my non-existent robot heart to cheat them so.
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Hey now, Doctor, don't look at me like that.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: Relax, I'm a Rhodes Island Operator too. Of course I can handle something like this.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: Doctor!
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Doctor!
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Wow, you two are really selling it.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: When did you get free?!
attributes.name: Archosauria

attributes.content: Hah. Sorry, somebody needs to learn to tie a knot.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: Did you know Tomimi was going to do this, Doctor?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: B-B-But how did you know?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.options: Well, first of all, there was the way you hesitated when Zumama came up.

attributes.content: Oh? Hesitated?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.options: And then when you panicked at Gavial during the ceremony.

attributes.content: Oh, I gave it to Lancet-2.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: Wahhh... That was just for you, Doctor. I don't normally let people put things inside me so easily.
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: It's... a rocket launcher?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Yep. Found it with Tomimi's tribe.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: So that means...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: You got it. The one who shot us down was this little runt right here.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: Tomimi.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Ohhhhh, I'm sorry, Gavial.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Come here.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Whimper)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: You're going over my knee.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial, please don't spank me, I know what I did was bad...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Them's the breaks.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Naughty little whelps get tail spankings!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Whimper)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Tail spanking, huh? Looks ouchie...
attributes.name: Ceobe

attributes.content: Are you going to do it again?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I won't do it agaaain! Waaahhh...!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Good.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Anyway, I think we're pretty much okay now, Doctor.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.options: Exhausting.;......;I'm surprised you didn't give her the whatever whirlwind thing.

attributes.content: Haha, well, it's definitely been a lot.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hey, Doctor, you're not falling asleep on your feet there, are you?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I wouldn't want to hurt little Tomimi, after all. Phew, I'm a little tired myself.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: This big guy... does look a little ugly at first, but the angular, rugged design, this cluttered but effective wiring, it has a special beauty to it when you look close.
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Real marriage material, I think.
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Oh, Lancet-2, go see if we can still salvage the engine.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: What? Are you telling me the engine's inside this big guy?!
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Sure is. And we blew it up.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Oh, poor engine. Poor big guy.
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Mr. Dylan, can you do me a favor?
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Dylan

attributes.content: Hey, Zumama, why are you standing there drooling like that?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial!
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Huh? What's up?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That... that...
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: What what?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That... that moving, talking machine is incredible!
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Oh, you mean Lancet-2? She's a friend of ours.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: C-Can I talk to her?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Knock yourself out.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Erm... Hello.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Hi?
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Are you... a machine?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: My product designation is Raythean Exister-S62 Model six-wheeled operation platform. I belong to Rhodes Island, codename Lancet-2.
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Wow!
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Yes. I do have a certain level of intelligence. As long as your questions aren't too hard, I should be able to answer them.
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Speaking of which, I am a medical operation platform, so my knowledge base is focused on medicine. Do keep that in mind.
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Is something wrong?
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: Can I hug you?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: What is she doing? Did a screw come loose?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Isn't it obvious? She's in awe of that machine.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Shocked as she was when she first saw a moving city, a machine that moves and talks on its own is even more striking!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: And forget her, I'm just as excited!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Oh, my beautiful young lady, might I have the honor of taking you on a date?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I know the most gorgeous spot in the rainforest. I'll take you there for a lovely afternoon!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Oh, y-you're asking me out?!
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: I don't know what to do here. I'm flattered... Doctor, should I accept?
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.options: Yes.;......;I'll never let you take my Lancet-2!

attributes.content: Don't butt in, High Priest, or you can't blame me for what happens to our friendship after all these years.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Honestly, I'm with the Doctor here.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Kinda wanna laugh.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Oh, Doctor, to hear you suddenly come out and say that... My heart isn't ready...
attributes.name: Lancet-2

attributes.content: So Gavial, your people you're with now can create this type of machine?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Huh? Err, I'm pretty sure Closure can, yeah.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Okay. I've made a decision.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Does this Rhodes Island place need more hands? I want to join.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I want to go with you, to learn about mechanical technology.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I've thought about leaving to go study in the outside world before, but I never seriously considered it because of the tribe. I think this is a great opportunity.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Th-Then I'm going too!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: If this is how it's going to be, then it's time for plan B... I'm going with Gavial!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Gavial, I fight really hard. I can definitely help you, Gavial!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Err, Doctor, what should I do here?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.options: They can come, but I don't know what might happen.;......;You made your bed, now lie in it.

attributes.content: Yeah. Might as well give them the operator tests.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: C'mon, Doctor, be nice.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Doooctooor!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Whatever. At least stick with the Doctor and try to learn something.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Right!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Hey, Gavial, do me a favor and tell me what this little squirt is saying.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Huh? Kemar?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I have to go with her.
attributes.name: Flint

attributes.content: She says she's going with you.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Oh. Cool. She packs a punch. I bet she'll make a fine operator.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: She said okay.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Good.
attributes.name: Flint

attributes.content: Hm? Wait a second. So Zumama's going, Tomimi's going, and Kemar's going, what about the tribes?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.options: You weren't worried about that when you left the first time.

attributes.content: Ahahaha, I was seeing red back then! Couldn't think at all.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: You're right, though... I can't just abandon my tribe.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Oh, I think you've got nothing to worry about in that department.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: It's no Gavial, but the Big Ugly is still pretty strong.
attributes.name: Archosauria A

attributes.content: That's for sure. I want to make one too.
attributes.name: Archosauria B

attributes.content: With the Temple destroyed, let's build machines instead. Whoever makes the most awesome one gets to be Great Chief?
attributes.name: Archosauria C

attributes.content: Hey, no! Fighting is way better!
attributes.name: Archosauria D

attributes.content: Oh, good point. I don't want to give up fighting. What should we do?
attributes.name: Archosauria C

attributes.content: All right, morons. Why not just fight and also build machines?!
attributes.name: Archosauria A

attributes.content: Yeah!
attributes.name: Group of Archosauria

attributes.content: See? Nothing to worry about at all.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: From what I've seen, the common folk are usually quick to adapt, even as the leaders hem and haw about the future.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: What if I told you the first Great Chief was actually a Tiacauh Brave who gave himself the title, prior to whom there was no custom to choose a Great Chief at all?
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: ...High Priest, why did you never tell me that before?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Oh, I never thought it was important. Is it? My point is that people are resilient, they'll go on living even if one of their traditions disappears.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: I've always thought of traditions as rituals that bring people together.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: But when that tradition carries on for a few decades, they start to think it's inviolable, it's unbreakable, it has to go on forever.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: But that's nonsense!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: So you tell me you want to blow up the Temple and I'm all in, both hands, both feet, and my tail too!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: Oh, no, if my hands and feet are in, my tail has to stay out... right? What if I'm laying down? Let's see!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: ...I get it.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Just how old are you?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: How old? I forget.
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: And honestly, these methods you have for keeping track of time mean nothing to me! Whether or not I happen to have forgotten when I was born!
attributes.name: High Priest

attributes.content: O...kay. But we still need someone to be the Great Chief.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hey, I heard Gavial and Zumama were fighting again. Is it already over?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Why are you looking at me like that, Gavial?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Say, Inam, are you interested in being Great Chief at all?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: So after going through all that, you got the engine back, performed your emergency repairs, and got on the road back home?
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Y-Yeah!
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Doctor, I do believe I told you what a precious piece of equipment that aircraft was before you left.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.options: There were extenuating circumstances.;......;Wasn't my fault.

attributes.content: Seeing as the aircraft is still in reparable condition, I won't be too hard on you. But the maintenance costs are coming out of your pay, and Blaze's.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Aww, and mine...?
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: An elite operator takes elite responsibility.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Agh, fine.
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: As for the three individuals you brought back, since you seem to think they have what it takes to be operators, I'll leave them to the Doctor.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Gavial, were you satisfied with your trip back home?
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Huh? Sure. But even I didn't think it'd go down like that. It was fun.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Honestly, I had a contingency plan in case the Doctor didn't bring you back.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Because I figured there was a possibility you'd want to stay there.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Huh? Kal'tsit, I thought you knew me better than that.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: You've never really adapted to life outside your tribe. Every day, you come into conflict with the world, in your own ferocious way.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: I'll put it this way: if someday you asked for a leave of absence, or if you just left, I wouldn't be surprised.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Hey, Doctor, maybe I'm not getting this right. Is Kal'tsit saying she cares about me?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: If there's nothing else, Dr. {@nickname}, you can go.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Tch, yeah, this is one of those times the Doctor likes to play dead.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Then I'm gonna go ahead and say you care about me.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That's our Kal'tsit, even confusing the Doctor.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Kal'tsit, I'm not going anywhere.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I had a reason to leave my tribe. I really did want to practice medicine.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Now that's not to say I really thought I could become a doctor, but I'm very happy I made that decision.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: From a modern medical standpoint, we pretty much have no doctors back home. If you get sick, you just let it run its course. Maybe try a few traditional remedies.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: If I never left, I wouldn't know what the world is really like.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I wouldn't know how many diseases are preventable or curable, I wouldn't know how people look down on Oripathy. I wouldn't know that saving lives makes me as happy as taking them.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: The world is definitely complicated, and I don't always know what motivates people, or why they fight.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: But I'm a doctor now. And my dream is to treat Oripathy.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Is there a better place in this wide world for me to study and practice medicine?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I'm afraid not.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Well how about that. And by the way, you all work a lot harder than I do. What's with you here worrying about me?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Honestly, I think I should be worrying about you, Kal'tsit.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: You didn't pick up my slack while I was away now, did you?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Good. I'm gonna give Zumama an Oripathy checkup. You have a nice chat now.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Oh, I'll see what Kemar's up to. Err, I guess I'm calling her Flint now. I'm worried she'll get into a fight, with the language barrier and all...
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: Doctor, Tomimi should be in her general studies class now. You check on her when you're done.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Welcome back.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Haha.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hey! What about me?!
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: You had another mission ready to go last week. You're technically very late.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Oh...
attributes.name: Blaze

attributes.content: In your eyes, you just went on a nonsensical journey.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: But, just like our Gavial, it was a showcase of the lively and diverse world we inhabit.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: We lose so much to the endless march of time. That which was once a fact of life in the past is now precious to us.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: We search for the light that slips through the breaks in the crowd and begin to see that as the norm.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: I hope you and your fellow operators learned a lesson from this trip: some things are not too far out of reach.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Kal'tsit, meeting time!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: Now then, Dr. {@nickname}, you have a lot of work waiting for you.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit

attributes.content: I hope you got enough rest on your vacation.
attributes.name: Kal'tsit
